## 8. API Route Rules

- All routes in `/app/api/` using Next.js Route Handlers
- Validate all inputs with Zod before processing
- Consistent response shape: `{ data: T, error: null }` / `{ data: null, error: { message: string } }`
- Player-facing routes MUST strip `is_hidden = true` items server-side — enforced at API level, not UI
- DM routes MUST verify `session.user.id` ownership before any write
- AI routes rate-limited to 5 requests/min per IP
- AI API keys are server-side only — never referenced in client components

---

## 9. Data Fetching Rules

- Server-side fetching via `createServerClient` from `@supabase/ssr`
- Client-side mutations via Supabase browser client in custom hooks
- All Supabase queries handle errors explicitly — never assume success
- Realtime subscriptions set up in Client Components in `useEffect` with cleanup
- Fetch all needed data in parallel with `Promise.all` — no waterfalls

---

## 10. Database & Supabase Rules

- RLS enabled on every table — policies written before any data access code
- Only the **anon key** (`NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`) is used in client code
- All RLS policies enforce that DMs can only access their own data
- Use `npx supabase` for all CLI commands — no global install
- All schema changes go through migrations in `/supabase/migrations/` — never alter tables in the dashboard
- Soft-delete items with `deleted_at timestamp` — never hard delete inventory
- All timestamps in UTC

---

## 11. Authentication Rules

- Google OAuth only via Supabase Auth
- Auth state checked in `middleware.ts` for all `/dm/*` and `/api/dm/*` routes
- Player routes are fully public — zero auth required
- Never store session data in localStorage — use httpOnly cookies via `@supabase/ssr`

---

## 12. AI Integration Rules

All AI prompt strings live in `/lib/prompts/` as named exports. Never write prompts inline.

- Use the AI client configured in `/lib/ai/` — do not instantiate AI clients directly in routes
- Always set token limits explicitly
- Always request JSON-only responses for structured data; parse with try/catch
- Store all generated images in Supabase Storage — never regenerate unless DM explicitly requests
- Show loading skeletons during all AI generation calls
- Disable generation buttons while a call is in flight

---

## 13. UI / Design System Rules

**Always defer to `DESIGN.md` for exact values.** The following are fallback defaults only.

### Fallback CSS Variables (define in `globals.css`)
```css
:root {
  --parchment: #f5e6c8;
  --parchment-dark: #e8d5a3;
  --ink: #2c1810;
  --gold: #c9a84c;
  --gold-light: #e8c97a;
  --ember: #8b3a0f;
  --shadow: #1a0f07;
  --muted: #6b5344;
}
```

### Typography
- Display / headings: **Cinzel** (Google Fonts)
- Body text: **Crimson Text** (Google Fonts)
- Prices / stats: **Courier Prime** (Google Fonts)

### Component Conventions
- Cards: `rounded-sm` for a worn, angular feel
- Borders: `border-gold/30` subtle metallic edge
- Primary buttons: ember or parchment background with gold text
- Rarity: common=gray, uncommon=green, rare=blue, very_rare=purple, legendary=orange
- Empty states use D&D flavor text — never generic "No results"

### Animations
- Page transitions: opacity fade 200ms
- Item cards: staggered `translateY` entrance, 50ms delay per card
- Loading skeletons: shimmer on parchment base

---

## 14. Mobile-First Rules

- All layouts designed for 375px minimum width first
- Touch targets minimum 44×44px
- No hover-only interactions on player-facing views
- QR share page: full-bleed, no chrome, single tap to copy URL
- Player shop view: single-column card scroll, sticky shopkeeper header

---

## 15. Error Handling Standards

Every route segment must have:
- `loading.tsx` — skeleton UI matching the real layout
- `error.tsx` — themed error state with retry
- `not-found.tsx` — D&D flavor 404 (e.g., "This shop has vanished from the realm...")

All async operations wrapped in try/catch.

---

## 16. Security Checklist

Before any commit:
- [ ] No API keys in client-side code
- [ ] All new tables have RLS policies
- [ ] Player API routes strip hidden items server-side
- [ ] DM API routes verify `user.id` ownership
- [ ] All user inputs validated via Zod before DB write

