## 17. Naming Conventions

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| React components | PascalCase | `ShopKeeperCard` |
| Hooks | `use` prefix + camelCase | `useShopRealtime` |
| Utility functions | camelCase | `calculateModifiedPrice` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_PRICE_MODIFIER` |
| DB tables | snake_case | `party_access` |
| API routes | kebab-case path segments | `/api/ai/generate-items` |
| CSS variables | kebab-case | `--parchment-dark` |
| Zod schemas | PascalCase + `Schema` suffix | `CreateShopSchema` |
| Types/Interfaces | PascalCase | `Shop`, `ShopItem` |

---

## 18. What Windsurf Should NEVER Do

- Never build a UI screen without first checking for a Stitch design via MCP
- Never hand-edit `DESIGN.md` — always regenerated from Stitch
- Never use the Pages Router or `getServerSideProps` / `getStaticProps`
- Never use `useState` for server-fetchable data
- Never reference AI API keys in client-side code
- Never hard delete items — always soft delete via `deleted_at`
- Never write AI prompts inline — they go in `/lib/prompts/`
- Never create shadcn components from scratch — install via the shadcn CLI
- Never commit `.env.local`
- Never use `eslint-disable` without naming the specific rule and explaining why
- **Never use `&&` to chain git commands** — PowerShell doesn't support it; use `;`
- **Never introduce alternative testing frameworks** — Jest only; no Vitest, no Mocha
